1
00:00:05,881 --> 00:00:09,885
(Y'all hittin' the bar today?)
(I have a gig)

2
00:00:13,764 --> 00:00:17,267
Being a Brave is a job where
you could get smoked at any second.

3
00:00:17,768 --> 00:00:21,438
A homie who was chilling yesterday
could be a ghost this morning.

4
00:00:24,691 --> 00:00:29,238
Pondering about when my turn gonna come
got me depressed as hell.

5
00:00:30,155 --> 00:00:31,280
In the end,

6
00:00:31,281 --> 00:00:34,742
maybe as a way to gear adrift
from that ate-up of reality,

7
00:00:34,743 --> 00:00:38,080
we end up staying posted to Ed Cyrus' bar.

8
00:00:46,797 --> 00:00:48,714
8,000 yen...

9
00:00:48,715 --> 00:00:50,175
What a rip-off.

10
00:00:53,276 --> 00:00:57,056
No money to carry into tomorrow, so hungry,
getting hit hard (Scum of the Brave)

11
00:00:57,057 --> 00:01:00,102
Playing bossa nova and
earning my day-to-day cash

12
00:01:00,853 --> 00:01:04,105
And the thugs
are running wild in the streets

13
00:01:04,106 --> 00:01:07,942
I'm just standing here,
staring at you with my dead-looking eyes

14
00:01:07,943 --> 00:01:12,739
There's not a single thing I can teach you

15
00:01:13,448 --> 00:01:14,907
Yeah...

16
00:01:14,908 --> 00:01:18,452
Let's just keep surviving over and over,
making fools of ourselves

17
00:01:18,453 --> 00:01:21,623
Since we're both not normal

18
00:01:23,250 --> 00:01:25,168
You can't save with "I-love-you"

19
00:01:25,169 --> 00:01:27,170
This town is sick

20
00:01:27,171 --> 00:01:30,673
Gradually, watching carefully,
get through it all

21
00:01:30,674 --> 00:01:34,177
That single moment in slow motion,
the battle's going good

22
00:01:34,178 --> 00:01:37,639
You and me,
we're so arrogant and so uncute

23
00:01:38,432 --> 00:01:40,100
Telling transparent lies

24
00:01:41,602 --> 00:01:45,479
Do you want to be strong?
Want to be loved?

25
00:01:45,480 --> 00:01:48,650
Stay quiet, you fool!

26
00:01:50,986 --> 00:01:52,987
Too early to say the "last of us"

27
00:01:52,988 --> 00:01:54,864
Today's day will soon be memorial

28
00:01:54,865 --> 00:01:58,035
Gradually, watching carefully,
bite into it and hang on

29
00:01:58,535 --> 00:02:00,953
Let's put on a poker face and go

30
00:02:00,954 --> 00:02:03,664
Still the same, you and me,

31
00:02:03,665 --> 00:02:06,083
we're so arrogant and so uncute

32
00:02:06,084 --> 00:02:07,835
Telling transparent lies

33
00:02:07,836 --> 00:02:10,047
You can't save with "I-love-you"

34
00:02:15,177 --> 00:02:17,513
You can't save a single soul

35
00:02:19,056 --> 00:02:21,016
Telling transparent lies

36
00:02:22,100 --> 00:02:27,022
(#6 Boot Camp of the Brave)

37
00:02:29,274 --> 00:02:32,528
Hey, long time no see, Yashiro.

38
00:02:33,529 --> 00:02:36,531
("Backstreet" Maruta)
(Unlicensed Brave)

39
00:02:36,532 --> 00:02:38,699
It sure is cold today.

40
00:02:38,700 --> 00:02:42,037
Master, can you make it a little warmer?

41
00:02:45,165 --> 00:02:47,708
Damn, you still kickin', Maruta?

42
00:02:47,709 --> 00:02:50,169
Thought you kicked the bucket already!

43
00:02:50,170 --> 00:02:53,048
Heh, been half a year, huh?

44
00:02:53,423 --> 00:02:56,551
Joe and Ishinoo.
Where are those bastards?

45
00:02:56,552 --> 00:02:58,511
Joe's on the grind,

46
00:02:58,512 --> 00:03:00,430
and I ain't heard from Ishinoo.

47
00:03:00,973 --> 00:03:03,015
It's been a while since I did,

48
00:03:03,016 --> 00:03:05,435
so he's prolly got bodied by now.

49
00:03:05,936 --> 00:03:08,397
Hey Ed, give me another glass!

50
00:03:19,199 --> 00:03:21,409
Hey, that's my beer.

51
00:03:21,410 --> 00:03:24,037
I know! Cheers!

52
00:03:26,707 --> 00:03:27,665
So...

53
00:03:27,666 --> 00:03:30,668
Where have you been slacking off
for the last six months?

54
00:03:30,669 --> 00:03:32,003
Hehe.

55
00:03:32,004 --> 00:03:33,463
Well...

56
00:03:34,715 --> 00:03:36,175
I got a job.

57
00:03:37,259 --> 00:03:38,885
A job?!

58
00:03:38,886 --> 00:03:41,638
You ain't even have a fixed address!

59
00:03:42,973 --> 00:03:44,432
Believe it or not,

60
00:03:44,433 --> 00:03:47,768
there was a company that actually
hired me as a contract worker.

61
00:03:47,769 --> 00:03:53,566
The job was lining up with others to
buy rare toys and tickets and stuff.

62
00:03:53,567 --> 00:03:54,775
Heh...

63
00:03:54,776 --> 00:03:58,571
So you finally quit being a Brave?

64
00:03:58,572 --> 00:04:00,656
Nah, actually...

65
00:04:00,657 --> 00:04:02,867
I got fired from that company.

66
00:04:02,868 --> 00:04:04,035
Huh?

67
00:04:04,036 --> 00:04:06,746
My boss told me to scam
some honest old lady,

68
00:04:06,747 --> 00:04:10,792
and sell her some shitty game console.

69
00:04:11,919 --> 00:04:13,837
Like hell I'd do that, right?

70
00:04:14,588 --> 00:04:17,507
So I crushed that asshole's eyeball,

71
00:04:17,508 --> 00:04:20,344
stole anything valuable, and ran.

72
00:04:21,762 --> 00:04:22,970
Whoa...

73
00:04:22,971 --> 00:04:25,724
I see. That sounds just like you.

74
00:04:26,183 --> 00:04:28,142
That's the divine punishment for him.

75
00:04:28,143 --> 00:04:29,353
I know, right?

76
00:04:32,981 --> 00:04:38,987
So today, I figured someone
might buy this thing I stole.

77
00:04:40,864 --> 00:04:42,532
King Rob's coming to Japan!

78
00:04:42,533 --> 00:04:48,497
Seven Medallions Grand Winter Season
finals spectator ticket!

79
00:04:52,835 --> 00:04:54,753
For real?!

80
00:04:56,088 --> 00:04:57,964
You want this that badly?

81
00:04:57,965 --> 00:04:59,632
Of course!

82
00:04:59,633 --> 00:05:03,387
King Rob is our hero!

83
00:05:04,179 --> 00:05:07,266
He's the guy who won three
world championships in a row!

84
00:05:08,016 --> 00:05:10,018
I'll buy it right now!
How much?!

85
00:05:11,687 --> 00:05:13,021
30,000 yen.

86
00:05:16,817 --> 00:05:20,027
If you're not buying,
I'll sell it to Joe or Ishinoo.

87
00:05:20,028 --> 00:05:21,237
Wait, wait!

88
00:05:21,238 --> 00:05:23,322
Can I pay next month?

89
00:05:23,323 --> 00:05:24,657
Nope.

90
00:05:24,658 --> 00:05:27,578
I don't have money for tomorrow's beer.

91
00:05:28,662 --> 00:05:31,957
I got a big lick poppin' next month.

92
00:05:32,332 --> 00:05:33,958
Rather than next month,

93
00:05:33,959 --> 00:05:36,461
how about you make
the money right now?

94
00:05:46,471 --> 00:05:48,849
We've been waiting for you, Master!

95
00:05:51,152 --> 00:05:54,020
I heard you started working
as a private tutor?

96
00:05:54,021 --> 00:05:55,939
Way to go, Yashiro.

97
00:05:57,232 --> 00:06:00,109
(Shogo Imamura)
(The Best Spears and Shields)

98
00:06:00,110 --> 00:06:01,820
In other words, it's practical training!

99
00:06:02,738 --> 00:06:03,864
Master!

100
00:06:04,406 --> 00:06:05,907
Next week at the Academy,

101
00:06:05,908 --> 00:06:09,286
there will be a sparring exam
using swords, held in a match format.

102
00:06:09,870 --> 00:06:11,537
It's an important event,

103
00:06:11,538 --> 00:06:14,750
that will determine whether
we advance or get expelled.

104
00:06:19,338 --> 00:06:23,591
So, I was hoping you could
personally give us sword training!

105
00:06:23,592 --> 00:06:25,636
Not happening! Go home!

106
00:06:26,512 --> 00:06:28,222
I'm asking too.

107
00:06:28,847 --> 00:06:30,432
We'll pay you.

108
00:06:31,266 --> 00:06:35,020
If I say nah, the chairman gonna
smoke me or what?

109
00:06:39,149 --> 00:06:43,987
Even if you refuse, I won't say a word.

110
00:06:45,697 --> 00:06:51,662
My dad only sees us as a nuisance
he can get rid of if we get expelled.

111
00:06:52,829 --> 00:06:54,164
Oh?

112
00:06:54,790 --> 00:06:56,707
Sounds just like a Brave.

113
00:06:56,708 --> 00:07:01,337
Which makes him
the worst scum of a father.

114
00:07:01,338 --> 00:07:04,091
Yeah, he's a scumbag.

115
00:07:05,759 --> 00:07:08,219
That's why I want you to teach us.

116
00:07:08,220 --> 00:07:09,930
You're a strong Brave.

117
00:07:11,682 --> 00:07:14,226
And someone we can trust.

118
00:07:16,770 --> 00:07:19,189
Aki said the same thing.

119
00:07:20,274 --> 00:07:21,942
Did she really?

120
00:07:22,442 --> 00:07:24,653
She ain't wrapped too tight upstairs.

121
00:07:30,951 --> 00:07:32,535
Huff...

122
00:07:32,536 --> 00:07:36,038
Plus, it takes more than
that lil' pocket money y'all got,

123
00:07:36,039 --> 00:07:37,696
to make this
first-rate Brave to...

124
00:07:57,686 --> 00:08:00,479
I'm a Brave, not a mentor.

125
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:02,608
Yes, we know.

126
00:08:03,317 --> 00:08:05,610
I'm probably trash at teaching.

127
00:08:05,611 --> 00:08:08,614
Yes, we're certain you are.

128
00:08:09,198 --> 00:08:11,116
Tuition is 100,000 yen for y'all three.

129
00:08:11,450 --> 00:08:13,619
Pay up or the deal's off.

130
00:08:22,336 --> 00:08:24,420
We'll pay 50,000 yen up front for now.

131
00:08:24,421 --> 00:08:26,381
The rest after the lesson.

132
00:08:29,689 --> 00:08:31,512
20,000... 30,000.

133
00:08:32,095 --> 00:08:35,139
Aight then, let's get this done quickly.

134
00:08:35,140 --> 00:08:37,643
We need a wide space and training weapons.

135
00:08:38,352 --> 00:08:40,019
Your school will do.

136
00:08:40,020 --> 00:08:42,563
Yes!
Then let's do that first thing tomorrow...

137
00:08:42,564 --> 00:08:43,565
Right now.

138
00:08:44,107 --> 00:08:45,025
Huh?

139
00:08:45,484 --> 00:08:47,902
Entering the school building
at night is prohibited.

140
00:08:47,903 --> 00:08:50,864
Who cares? We'll just break in.

141
00:08:51,365 --> 00:08:53,658
If you can't sneak into a school,

142
00:08:53,659 --> 00:08:55,994
how are you going to sneak
into a Demon King's castle?

143
00:09:03,001 --> 00:09:04,377
Yes.

144
00:09:04,378 --> 00:09:06,380
I think that's a good idea.

145
00:09:10,509 --> 00:09:12,511
It feels like a real boot camp!

146
00:09:15,013 --> 00:09:20,018
(Scum of the Brave)

147
00:09:26,733 --> 00:09:29,151
Heh, wall-to-wall tatami, I see.

148
00:09:29,152 --> 00:09:30,737
They must be swimming in that dough.

149
00:09:34,867 --> 00:09:37,160
Please give us your guidance!

150
00:09:37,661 --> 00:09:41,789
We're hoping for some ultimate move
we can learn quickly or something!

151
00:09:41,790 --> 00:09:44,167
Ain't no such thing.

152
00:09:44,168 --> 00:09:46,169
An ultimate move...

153
00:09:46,170 --> 00:09:47,546
Tell me...

154
00:09:47,921 --> 00:09:48,880
What's that like?!

155
00:09:48,881 --> 00:09:50,174
I told you there ain't one.

156
00:09:53,677 --> 00:09:56,137
Strap on them protectors already.

157
00:09:56,138 --> 00:09:57,723
We'll kick this off with sparring.

158
00:09:58,140 --> 00:10:00,517
I can take y'all three at once.

159
00:10:01,018 --> 00:10:02,060
Yes!

160
00:10:02,769 --> 00:10:04,813
So we just spar with you?

161
00:10:05,564 --> 00:10:07,273
What about you?

162
00:10:07,274 --> 00:10:09,318
Aren't you putting on a protector?

163
00:10:09,860 --> 00:10:12,321
Don't sleep on a pro.

164
00:10:14,239 --> 00:10:15,657
Come on and get me.

165
00:10:16,325 --> 00:10:17,200
Yes!

166
00:10:17,201 --> 00:10:20,829
Then the honor of going first
goes to me, Jogamine!

167
00:10:27,711 --> 00:10:29,713
First, Indo.

168
00:10:30,088 --> 00:10:31,840
She's bold, but...

169
00:10:40,516 --> 00:10:44,311
You're easy to read,
coming straight like that.

170
00:10:50,359 --> 00:10:53,237
Then the star player, Jogamine, is up!

171
00:10:55,239 --> 00:10:57,574
Why're ya doubling down
on that same mistake, you clown?

172
00:11:01,870 --> 00:11:03,747
Second, Jogamine.

173
00:11:10,003 --> 00:11:14,007
A style that parries attacks with
a shield while aiming for counters.

174
00:11:17,302 --> 00:11:18,595
This girl...

175
00:11:32,401 --> 00:11:37,865
You don't pull counter moves on
somebody stronger than you.

176
00:11:38,615 --> 00:11:40,908
You'll break down easily,

177
00:11:40,909 --> 00:11:42,870
and get taken by hand-to-hand moves.

178
00:11:43,579 --> 00:11:48,166
Well, your raw strength on E3
might be higher than mine, though.

179
00:11:49,585 --> 00:11:50,752
Everything else aside.

180
00:11:51,253 --> 00:11:52,962
Take this a bit more seriously.

181
00:11:52,963 --> 00:11:54,006
Huh?

182
00:12:11,315 --> 00:12:12,857
That's cheating!

183
00:12:12,858 --> 00:12:15,234
Throwing swords is forbidden
in real matches!

184
00:12:15,235 --> 00:12:18,529
Oh, that's a textbook amateur talk.

185
00:12:18,530 --> 00:12:20,616
If it pisses you off that much,

186
00:12:21,033 --> 00:12:22,868
try landing a hit on me.

187
00:12:37,841 --> 00:12:39,760
Well, that was a good workout.

188
00:12:40,260 --> 00:12:44,722
Hey, what's with you?!
All you've done is use dirty tricks!

189
00:12:44,723 --> 00:12:47,016
We can't use that in a match!

190
00:12:47,017 --> 00:12:48,100
You're right.

191
00:12:48,101 --> 00:12:50,228
You can't do what I did as a reference.

192
00:12:50,229 --> 00:12:51,187
Huh?

193
00:12:51,188 --> 00:12:54,733
But I figured out the reason
why you girls are falling behind.

194
00:12:55,442 --> 00:12:57,068
The reason?

195
00:12:57,069 --> 00:12:59,654
I see! That's our master for you!

196
00:12:59,655 --> 00:13:04,450
Then please give your honest opinion
to me, your first disciple!

197
00:13:04,451 --> 00:13:05,369
Yeah.

198
00:13:05,994 --> 00:13:08,955
First, Sarah, you're too scared.

199
00:13:08,956 --> 00:13:10,206
What?!

200
00:13:10,207 --> 00:13:12,124
Who are you calling scared?!

201
00:13:12,125 --> 00:13:13,377
That. What you did there.

202
00:13:15,671 --> 00:13:20,008
Pointlessly trying to intimidate others
means you actually wanna avoid conflict.

203
00:13:21,218 --> 00:13:23,428
Anyway, let's talk about
the sparring we did.

204
00:13:23,929 --> 00:13:26,265
You always go third when
it's time to strike, right?

205
00:13:28,016 --> 00:13:30,811
That's why you could always
swing down with full power.

206
00:13:34,606 --> 00:13:37,734
That's because I was trying
to knock you down...

207
00:13:38,277 --> 00:13:41,696
Meaning, you wanna
end it all in one hit.

208
00:13:41,697 --> 00:13:45,242
You don't wanna get hit back,
so you rush to close it quick.

209
00:13:47,578 --> 00:13:52,249
And if it looks like you can't win,
you tap out fast.

210
00:13:54,334 --> 00:13:57,087
Sounds like you were taught
that kind of self-defense.

211
00:13:59,756 --> 00:14:03,552
You were probably taught
not to fight someone you can't beat.

212
00:14:08,640 --> 00:14:11,393
Anyway, you should fix that.

213
00:14:12,144 --> 00:14:16,731
Basically, you gotta fight thinkin'
about forcing a stalemate.

214
00:14:16,732 --> 00:14:18,400
Next, Indo.

215
00:14:19,693 --> 00:14:22,029
Your problem is...

216
00:14:23,864 --> 00:14:25,032
Nothing in particular.

217
00:14:25,824 --> 00:14:29,286
Be honest, your practical
scores aren't bad, right?

218
00:14:31,288 --> 00:14:33,915
Yukine's problem is academics.

219
00:14:33,916 --> 00:14:35,626
She's shaky on multiplication tables.

220
00:14:36,710 --> 00:14:38,085
I can do that much.

221
00:14:38,086 --> 00:14:39,378
Liar.

222
00:14:39,379 --> 00:14:40,713
When I tried teaching you,

223
00:14:40,714 --> 00:14:43,258
you were solving them with some
weird code-like method.

224
00:14:44,551 --> 00:14:45,927
That was a coincidence.

225
00:14:45,928 --> 00:14:49,056
There's no such thing
as a coincidence in math.

226
00:14:52,643 --> 00:14:54,101
So first...

227
00:14:54,102 --> 00:14:56,062
Just shut up and listen to me!

228
00:14:56,063 --> 00:14:58,689
Raise your hand when you want to speak!

229
00:14:58,690 --> 00:15:01,693
Anyway, you don't really have any issues.

230
00:15:02,444 --> 00:15:03,903
But Instructor,

231
00:15:03,904 --> 00:15:05,948
I want to become stronger.

232
00:15:06,490 --> 00:15:09,910
You're stronger than me right now,
so I want you to teach me.

233
00:15:11,537 --> 00:15:14,665
"Right now", you said?
Talk about cheeky.

234
00:15:15,415 --> 00:15:16,916
Well, someday.

235
00:15:16,917 --> 00:15:18,752
Someday when?

236
00:15:19,878 --> 00:15:21,255
Someday.

237
00:15:23,340 --> 00:15:24,924
Lastly, Jogamine.

238
00:15:24,925 --> 00:15:25,925
Yes!

239
00:15:25,926 --> 00:15:28,177
You're so hopeless.

240
00:15:28,178 --> 00:15:29,304
Not even worth discussing.

241
00:15:31,765 --> 00:15:33,140
You can't be serious!

242
00:15:33,141 --> 00:15:34,810
I am dead serious.

243
00:15:35,310 --> 00:15:36,477
How do I put it...

244
00:15:36,478 --> 00:15:42,150
You ain't fightin' to kill
or wreck your opponent.

245
00:15:44,152 --> 00:15:46,988
That's what I've noticed since
the Amber Thorn incident.

246
00:15:46,989 --> 00:15:50,826
Don't tell me you don't wanna kill people?

247
00:15:52,244 --> 00:15:54,538
If that's the case, quit being a Brave.

248
00:15:56,582 --> 00:15:59,418
Your problem is beyond skill.

249
00:16:01,920 --> 00:16:03,713
But Master...

250
00:16:03,714 --> 00:16:06,300
I was taught that a Brave represents hope.

251
00:16:06,800 --> 00:16:07,800
Huh?

252
00:16:07,801 --> 00:16:12,931
If peace can be built without hurting
anyone, wouldn't that be best?

253
00:16:13,682 --> 00:16:16,058
Being a Brave is already a thorny path.

254
00:16:16,059 --> 00:16:21,315
If so, shouldn't we always strive
for the best possible outcome?

255
00:16:24,651 --> 00:16:26,570
This brat is seriously delusional.

256
00:16:27,321 --> 00:16:30,199
Maybe she needs harsher training.

257
00:16:32,242 --> 00:16:33,285
What's this?

258
00:16:34,411 --> 00:16:36,205
That face...

259
00:16:37,539 --> 00:16:38,790
I think I've seen it somewhere...

260
00:16:50,427 --> 00:16:51,344
Hey!

261
00:16:51,345 --> 00:16:54,263
We're done for if we're caught.

262
00:16:54,264 --> 00:16:55,348
Perfect timing.

263
00:16:55,349 --> 00:16:57,725
Sarah, Jogamine...

264
00:16:57,726 --> 00:17:01,230
You two handle the guys
coming now and shut 'em up.

265
00:17:01,730 --> 00:17:04,607
Solve your own issues in real combat...

266
00:17:04,608 --> 00:17:07,236
If you screw up and
get exposed, you're expelled.

267
00:17:07,736 --> 00:17:08,903
Oh?

268
00:17:08,904 --> 00:17:12,491
Maybe I'm actually cut out for teaching?

269
00:17:20,749 --> 00:17:26,003
But Master, even if it's for training,
hurting innocent guards is kinda...

270
00:17:26,004 --> 00:17:29,924
They've let us infiltrate,
so they're not exactly innocent.

271
00:17:29,925 --> 00:17:32,261
Think of it as their training too.

272
00:17:33,178 --> 00:17:34,887
That's one way to think about it...

273
00:17:34,888 --> 00:17:37,641
Don't let him talk you into it, Aki!

274
00:17:39,643 --> 00:17:42,436
Instructor, what about my training?

275
00:17:42,437 --> 00:17:44,772
Huh? You're fine for now.

276
00:17:44,773 --> 00:17:48,025
I don't want to be the only one
with nothing to write home about.

277
00:17:48,026 --> 00:17:50,279
Will you train me again?

278
00:17:50,863 --> 00:17:53,197
If you can follow my orders.

279
00:17:53,198 --> 00:17:55,284
Just go sit over there in the squat.

280
00:17:55,659 --> 00:17:56,743
Got it.

281
00:17:57,995 --> 00:17:59,662
As expected of Yukine!

282
00:17:59,663 --> 00:18:01,765
Even I'm kinda freaked out by how...

283
00:18:09,423 --> 00:18:11,967
Was it really here?

284
00:18:12,301 --> 00:18:15,470
Yeah. I definitely saw a light.

285
00:18:16,096 --> 00:18:18,097
You're so serious.

286
00:18:18,098 --> 00:18:20,558
This is outside the contract, right?

287
00:18:20,559 --> 00:18:22,060
Well, whatever.

288
00:18:23,061 --> 00:18:25,272
Want to grab a meal together after this?

289
00:18:29,026 --> 00:18:31,861
They might be companions of
the man from yesterday.

290
00:18:31,862 --> 00:18:34,614
He seemed quite skilled, didn't he?

291
00:18:34,615 --> 00:18:36,450
Well, yeah.

292
00:18:36,950 --> 00:18:39,620
It still hurts, so how about you nurse me?

293
00:18:43,123 --> 00:18:46,375
See? They've already run off.

294
00:18:46,376 --> 00:18:48,336
No need to go this far.

295
00:18:48,337 --> 00:18:50,922
Don't say unnecessary things, Id.

296
00:18:50,923 --> 00:18:52,007
Huh?

297
00:18:52,799 --> 00:18:54,510
That woman's voice...

298
00:18:55,260 --> 00:18:56,637
Ether hoarse.

299
00:18:57,804 --> 00:19:00,431
It's what happened to Demon Kings
who've had sloppy surgery,

300
00:19:00,432 --> 00:19:03,727
or addicts who use illegal amounts of E3.

301
00:19:06,063 --> 00:19:10,609
And from the way they talk,
they don't sound like teachers or guards.

302
00:19:11,360 --> 00:19:14,029
They might still be nearby.

303
00:19:14,696 --> 00:19:16,114
Let's track them.

304
00:19:22,246 --> 00:19:23,497
Aight. Go!

305
00:19:27,042 --> 00:19:29,044
Argh, screw this!

306
00:19:35,968 --> 00:19:38,594
Damn, she actually goin' on offense.

307
00:19:38,595 --> 00:19:40,430
That's the fruit of my teaching!

308
00:19:43,559 --> 00:19:45,769
Maybe not as ripe as I thought.

309
00:19:46,395 --> 00:19:48,021
That woman's got skills.

310
00:19:50,357 --> 00:19:51,441
Ouch!

311
00:19:53,861 --> 00:19:55,361
You illegal intruders!

312
00:19:55,362 --> 00:19:57,613
Do you intend to oppose the Academy?!

313
00:19:57,614 --> 00:19:59,323
State your names!

314
00:19:59,324 --> 00:20:01,576
Press the attack, you idiot.

315
00:20:01,577 --> 00:20:04,120
Tch, students.

316
00:20:04,121 --> 00:20:05,539
Why are they here?

317
00:20:08,333 --> 00:20:10,210
Indo, get ready.

318
00:20:11,086 --> 00:20:13,839
They don't look like amateurs.

319
00:20:16,091 --> 00:20:18,427
We're retreating! You may use your E3!

320
00:20:19,678 --> 00:20:21,053
Can I kill them?

321
00:20:21,054 --> 00:20:24,015
Idiot. Cover Jogamine and fall back.

322
00:20:24,016 --> 00:20:25,309
Understood.

323
00:20:32,024 --> 00:20:34,818
Hey, don't chicken out! Stand up!

324
00:20:41,867 --> 00:20:43,035
You...

325
00:20:49,958 --> 00:20:52,294
It hurts...

326
00:20:53,462 --> 00:20:54,671
Screw this...!

327
00:21:00,844 --> 00:21:03,764
Is this some kind of trend or what?

328
00:21:06,433 --> 00:21:08,059
Mental rental

329
00:21:08,060 --> 00:21:09,769
As a beautiful girl,
my policy is to be undefeated

330
00:21:09,770 --> 00:21:11,270
Entitled "Invincible Girl"

331
00:21:11,271 --> 00:21:13,022
I'm renting you in my heart

332
00:21:13,023 --> 00:21:14,440
Mental rental

333
00:21:14,441 --> 00:21:16,317
